news.title: NCLAT stays order to restart Rajesh Business' bankruptcy process
news.para: The Rs 492 crore resolution plan by a Rare ARC-Check-Inn Hotels Pvt Ltd consortium had envisaged about 79% recovery on lender dues of more than Rs 621 crore. But more than a year after the committee of creditors (CoC) had approved the plan, a Mumbai bench of the NCLT ordered a fresh process citing procedural issues that ICICI Bank had challenged.

news.title: Vietnam's Truong My Lan faces second trial for $12.5 billion financial fraud
news.para: Her arrest and conviction was one of the highest profile cases in an anti-corruption drive that has intensified since 2022. The so-called blazing furnace campaign has also singed the highest echelons of Vietnamese politics and led to the resignation of a former president who was implicated in it.

news.title: BBMP to geotag properties for issuing digital e-khatas in Bengaluru
news.para: As part of this process, BBMP staff will soon visit properties across the city to capture their GPS coordinates. This data will serve as a unique identity marker for each property, which is crucial for online delivery of e-khata services.

news.title: Maharashtra government allocates Rs 188.3 crore funds to MMRCL, Rs 165 crore to Pune Metro
news.para: In a Govt Resolution issued on Thursday, the state urban development dept said a decision has been made to allocate funds to Mumbai Metro Rail Corporation Limited and Maharashtra Metro Rail Corporation (MahaMetro) as per the details shown in the budget for the year 2024-25 under the one percent additional tax surcharge.

news.title: Residents of MUDA approved layouts in Mysuru outskirts struggle for amenities
news.para: A dispute between Muda and the newly-formed Hootagalli City Municipal Council (CMC) has left residents, who are paying taxes to Muda, without essential services, residents complained. Neither Muda nor the Hootagalli CMC have stepped in to resolve the issue, localities alleged.

news.title: Shine City Group's vice president arrested in investment scam
news.para: ADCP North Jitendra Kumar Dubey said that there was a reward of 50,000 on the accused Manish Jaiswal, and the police had been searching for him for about a year. He said cases of fraud had been registered against Manish in Lucknow and Prayagraj.

news.title: Developers in NCR allowed non-polluting work during construction ban: CAQM
news.para: This year, the authority has listed activities which will be banned, instead of imposing a blanket ban on construction activities if the air quality turns "severe" (stage III), said industry executives, This will allow developers to continue with some interior work, they said.

news.title: Mumbai Grahak Panchayat defends MahaRERA conciliation forum
news.para: "MahaRERA Conciliation Forum originates from Sec. 32 (g) of RERA, 2016, which mandates state RERA authorities to recommend to the state govt measures to facilitate amicable conciliation of disputes between promoters and allottees through dispute settlement forum set up by the consumer or promoters association," said Deshpande.

news.title: YEIDA offers 1,200 flats near under-construction Noida airport
news.para: A total of 276 affordable 1BHK flats, with a total area of 29.8 sqm and a usable living space of 21.6 sqm, are priced at Rs 23.4 lakh for ground-floor units and Rs 20.7 lakh for first, second, and third-floor flats.

news.title: Adani Group to acquire 46.64% stake in ITD Cementation India for Rs 5,888 crore
news.para: At current market value, a successful deal would be pegged at 5,888.57 crore ($700 million), inclusive of a fully subscribed open offer that will follow a promoter stake purchase.

news.title: MahaRERA to launch IT-powered project grading system in October
news.para: The gradation will be done using IT tools after assessing technical, financial and legal details as well as project overview provided by developers, said MahaRERA chairman Ajoy Mehta, who will retire on Friday.

news.title: Arkade Developers IPO gets subscribed 106.40 times on last day
news.para: Qualified institutional buyers subscribed the offer 163.16 times while the quota for non-institutional investors fetched 162.75 times subscription. The portion for retail individual investors received 50.65 times subscription.

news.title: NGT issues notice to Centre, Delhi LG over DDA's Kusumpur Pahadi rehabilitation scheme
news.para: According to the scheme, 2,800 dwelling units are to be constructed over 18.96 acres where the jhuggi-jhopdi (JJ) cluster currently stands in Kusumpur Pahadi. They are home to around one lakh people.

news.title: Indian retail sector needs 55 million sq ft of grade-A malls till 2027: Report
news.para: H1 2024 saw no new mall supply enter the market. Country's total grade-A mall inventory, currently stands at 61 million sq ft across top eight cities, translating to a mere 0.5 sq ft of RSPC, which is much lower even when compared with smaller countries such as Indonesia, the Philippines and Vietnam.

news.title: Oswal Pumps files IPO papers with Sebi; aims Rs 1,000 crore via fresh issue
news.para: The IPO is a combination of fresh issue of equity shares worth Rs 1,000 crore and an offer-for-sale (OFS) of up to 1.13 crore equity shares by promoter Vivek Gupta, according to the draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) filed on Tuesday.

news.title: Macrotech Developers to acquire stake in three Ivanhoe entities for Rs 239.56 crore
news.para: The company will acquire 10% equity stake and other securities in Bellissimo Digital Infrastructure Development Management for Rs 14.77 crore, 33.33% equity stake and other securities in Palava Induslogic 4 for Rs 142.52 crore and 33.33% equity stake and other securities in Bellissimo In City FC Mumbai 1 for Rs 82.27 crore.

news.title: K Raheja Corp's Inorbit Malls acquires retail property for Rs 400 crore in Hubli
news.para: The mall is strategically situated on Gokul Main Road and its catchment extends to cover Hubli and Dharwad, the second largest urban region in Karnataka.

news.title: Developers in Gurugram use new TDR policy to increase saleable area
news.para: As per the policy of Haryana government, landowners whose land is acquired for development projects can receive TDR certificates from the government instead of monetary compensation.
